- uses configmap :
- as mount as volume (we can create --from-file=file_name.txt) - spec.volumes.configMap.name
- as env (a single item) - (create using --from-literal=key=value) - need to use env 
- as env whole file - (multiple items) --from-env-file - only configMapRef

1. Mounted as a Volume (From Files)This method is used when you want the configuration data to appear as files on the container's file system.Imperative Creation:bashkubectl create configmap my-volume-config --from-file=file_name.txt
Use code with caution.Pod Specification Blueprint:yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: volume-config-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: app-container
    image: nginx
    volumeMounts:
    - name: config-volume
      mountPath: /etc/config     # The directory where the file will appear
  volumes:
  - name: config-volume
    configMap:
      name: my-volume-config     # Must match your ConfigMap name
Use code with caution.2. As an Environment Variable (Single Item)This pattern injects a specific single key-value pair into the container as an isolated environment variable.Imperative Creation:bashkubectl create configmap my-single-env-config --from-literal=DB_PORT=5432
Use code with caution.Pod Specification Blueprint:yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: single-env-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: app-container
    image: nginx
    command : ["/bin/sh","-c"]
    args :
        - echo "port = $DATABASE_PORT";sleep 3600
    env:
    - name: DATABASE_PORT        # The name inside your container
      valueFrom:
        configMapKeyRef:
          name: my-single-env-config
          key: DB_PORT           # The exact key stored inside the ConfigMap
Use code with caution.3. As Environment Variables (Whole File / Multiple Items)This strategy parses an entire environment file (containing KEY=VALUE rows) and exposes every line as an individual environment variable inside the container.Imperative Creation:bashkubectl create configmap my-all-env-config --from-env-file=.env
Use code with caution.Pod Specification Blueprint:yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: all-env-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: app-container
    image: nginx
    envFrom:                     # Notice it is envFrom instead of env
    - configMapRef:              # Notice it is configMapRef, not configMapKeyRef
        name: my-all-env-config
